*Important dates*

- Deadline for abstract submission: *May 25, 2018*

- Deadline for early registration: *June 10, 2018*

*Accommodation*: book your accommodation as soon as possible! S. Miguel
(and Azores) is a very touristic destination and the conference takes
place during the high season. Also, there is a limited number of rooms
with special rates secured for the CT participants; you may find those,
and others, at http://www.mat.uc.pt/~ct2018/accommodation.html
<http://www.mat.uc.pt/%7Ect2018/accommodation.html>. These special rates
are guaranteed for bookings made until *March 31, 2018*. Reservations
should be dealt directly with each hotel.

*Abstract submission: *follow the indications at
http://www.mat.uc.pt/~ct2018/dates.html
<http://www.mat.uc.pt/%7Ect2018/dates.html>to submit an abstract.
Acceptance of abstracts will be communicated by *June 6, 2018*. Talks
are 30min (25min exposition + 5min discussion).

*Registration*: fill the registration form found at
http://www.mat.uc.pt/~ct2018/registration.html
<http://www.mat.uc.pt/%7Ect2018/registration.html> and make a bank
transfer to pay the fee. Early registration fee - 200??? (by *June 10,
2018*); late registration fee - 250??? (after June 10, 2018). The fee
includes conference documentation, welcome reception (Sunday evening),
coffee breaks and lunches, excursion (Thursday afternoon) and conference
dinner (Friday evening).

All information concerning CT2018 may be found at
http://www.mat.uc.pt/~ct2018/.


Looking forward to seeing you all there!

Best regards,

